EmergencyConditions - Class in hospital.model
This class stores and provides information about various emergency conditions recognized by the hospital's ER.
EmergencyConditions(String) - Constructor for class hospital.model.EmergencyConditions
Creates a new EmergencyConditions object based on comma separated data provided in a specified configuration file.
EmergencyRoomLog - Class in hospital.model
This class stores log information about Patients served by the Emergency Room doctors.
EmergencyRoomLog() - Constructor for class hospital.model.EmergencyRoomLog
Creates an empty ER Log.
EmptyLogException - Exception in hospital.exceptions
This exception is used to signal that an invalid request has been made to a log object.
EmptyLogException() - Constructor for exception hospital.exceptions.EmptyLogException
Constructs a EmptyLogException containing a default message that "No data is in the log!".
EmptyWaitingRoomException - Exception in hospital.exceptions
This exception arises when a waiting room cannot support a requested action because there are no patients currently waiting.
EmptyWaitingRoomException() - Constructor for exception hospital.exceptions.EmptyWaitingRoomException
Produces a new EmptyWaitingRoomException with a default message of indicating that the waiting room is empty.
